<subSubSection id="C355653DFFBC8D24F7A5AF979636B746" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BF036B6FFBC8D24F7A5AF979636B746" blockId="2.[1996,2589,1673,2101]" lastBlockId="2.[1378,2590,2115,3321]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">
<taxonomicName id="4C4F4D35FFBC8D24F7A5AF9799C8B92F" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1920" box="[2000,2247,1791,1824]" class="Mammalia" family="Calomyscidae" genus="Calomyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="baluchi">Calomyscus baluchi</taxonomicName>
was originally described as a distinct but closely related species to 
<taxonomicName id="4C4F4D35FFBC8D24F7A5AE26997DB960" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1905" box="[2000,2162,1870,1903]" class="Mammalia" family="Calomyscidae" genus="Calomyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="2" pageNumber="154" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bailwardi">C. bailwardi</taxonomicName>
that could be differentiated by its smaller ears and longer palatine foramina. Latter revisions treated it as a subspecies of C. bailward: until N. N. Vorontsov and colleagues in 1979 conducted a comprehensive revision of the genus that elevated it to a distinct species. They noted, however, that the two species were morphologically very similar but their distributions were separated by presence of a morphologically distinct species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C4F4D35FFBC8D24F736A1E696CCB6A4" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1920" box="[1859,1987,2190,2219]" class="Mammalia" family="Calomyscidae" genus="Calomyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hotsoni">C. hotsoni</taxonomicName>
. Results of molecular phylogenetics analyses support the specific status of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4F4D35FFBC8D24F749A1D996B1B6DD" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1920" box="[1852,1982,2225,2258]" class="Mammalia" family="Calomyscidae" genus="Calomyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="baluchi">C. baluchi</taxonomicName>
and its close relationship with 
<taxonomicName id="4C4F4D35FFBC8D24F90CA1D99B19B6DD" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1905" box="[2425,2582,2225,2258]" class="Mammalia" family="Calomyscidae" genus="Calomyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="2" pageNumber="154" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bailwardi">C. bailwardi</taxonomicName>
. No karyotypic data are available. Two subspecies recognized, but preliminary phylogeographic analysis failed to provide support for their recognition, analyses with greater geographic coverage are needed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C355653DFFBC8D24F51CA03B9802B402" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" type="multiple">
